<TITLE> Another injured in hotel explosions dies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 4 (bdnews24.com)  Another staff member of Hotel Orchard Plaza injured during the Sunday night explosions died Wednesday morning. Hotel boy Kiran died while undergoing treatment at Dhaka Medical College Hospital. Kiran, son of Md Abul Kashem came from Noakhali. Two separate probes initiated by the police and Titas Gas Transmission and Distribution Authority have started their investigative activities. The police investigators were asked to submit their report within a week while Titas was asked to submit its probe report in two days. Earlier, house keeper Ali Azam Ahmed of the same hotel who'd sustained serious burn injuries died Monday. About 30 people were injured in the twin explosions at the Orchard Plaza Sunday. The first explosion occurred at around 9:15 pm while the second at around 11:30 pm, when the hotel staff went in to assess the damages injuring fire fighters, newsmen, police, RAB members and hotel staffers. bdnews24.c
